                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Dated by the relationship to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2180.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 4 December [1857]</ref>, and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2181.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. D. Hooker, [6 December 1857]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD eventually used six volumes of Candolle and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1215.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Candolle 1824–73</ref> for his calculations. They covered the orders Leguminosae, Rosaceae, Borragineae, Scrophulariaceae, Acanthaceae, Verbenaceae, Labiatae, Solanaceae, Proteaceae, and Polygonaceae (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5799.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Natural selection</hi></ref>, pp. 153–4).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4651.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ledebour 1842–53</ref>, A. Gray 1856a, and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4418.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Koch 1843–4</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD was not able to incorporate data from <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_565.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Bentham 1858</ref> into his table on the number of species and varieties in large and small genera (see <hi rend="italic">Natural</hi> <hi rend="italic">selection</hi>, pp. 149, 152). By the time <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_565.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Bentham 1858</ref> was published, CD was busy writing <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2177.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to George Bentham, 1 December [1857]</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2181.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. D. Hooker, [6 December 1857]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2378.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Ferdinand Jakob Heinrich von Mueller, 8 December [1857]</ref>. CD’s letter to Charles Moore, director of the botanic gardens at Sydney, Australia, has not been located.</note>
        </div>        
            
